observations.recommendation:
Written justification be submitted by the following:

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) for the payment of heavy equipment to RedCat International Limited, a foreign supplier, instead to Avantrac Heavy Machinery, Inc., the winning local bidder and on the absence of Warranty Security for the procurement of heavy equipment;

The Municipal Mayor on the absence of date of acceptance per Notice of Delivery and Acceptance for the heavy equipment;

The certifying officials on the varying delivery dates per Certificate of Acceptance, Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment and NDAs;

The officials concerned on the non-imposition of liquidated damages on the delayed delivery of heavy equipment.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Inventory Committee ensure the conduct of the required annual physical inventory of PPEs;
The Inventory Committee submit the RPCPPE to the Audit Team, based on the results of physical inventory of PPEs;
The Inventory Committee expedite and complete the process of consolidation of all the necessary reports relative to the conduct of one-time cleansing of PPE account balances;
The Inventory Committee submit the pertinent reports and documents relative to the conduct of one-time cleansing of PPE account to the Municipal Accountant for reconciliation;
The Municipal Accountant effect the necessary adjustment in the PPE accounts and fairly present the balances in the LGU books, based on the reports and documents prepared by the Inventory Committee;
The Municipal Accountant ensure that the total balance of PPELCs tally with the controlling PPE accounts in the General Ledger, to establish proper reconciliation of records.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Treasurer, being the head of the Inventory Committee,  properly plan and ensure the conduct of periodic physical count of inventories, maintain stock cards and prepare RIS and SSMI, pursuant to Sections 114, 121 and 124 of the MNGAS;
The Municipal Accountant assign specific accounting personnel who shall be in-charge in maintaining the stock cards for inventories in order to comply with Section 114 of the MNGAS.

4.3	We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Treasurer furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year after due consideration of payments for delinquent taxes, at the beginning of the year, in accordance with Section 20 of the Manual on NGAS, Volume 1;
The Municipal Accountant immediately record the Real Property Tax and Special Education Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year based on the certified list furnished by the Municipal Treasurer to timely recognize the tax receivables.

9.6	We recommended that Management:
Submit an explanation on the: (a) delayed and incomplete submission of documents required for the release of the last tranche of funds for the Dagohoy Resettlement Project - Phase 1 which resulted in the non-payment of the contractor in the amount of ₱995,472.83; (b) delayed approval of the Code of Policies on the Beneficiary Selection for the Dagohoy Resettlement Project - Phase 1; and (c) insufficient action on the part of the management which resulted in the lapse of NHA fund allocation amounting to ₱10 million;
Expedite the processing of required documents and reports and intensify the coordination efforts with the NHA in order to fully implement the Dagohoy Resettlement Project – Phase 1 and 2 and immediately deliver services and benefits to the intended beneficiaries.

10.7	We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Engineer submit the supporting documents for the Request for Time Extension, specifically the tabulation of unworkable days and weather charts for those days, being the recommendatory LGU official for the issuance of Time Extension;
Management require the contractor to expedite the project completion, considering the issuance of ECC by the DENR;
The Municipal Accountant ascertain any unwarranted delays and compute liquidated damages, whenever applicable, which shall be deducted from payments due to the contractor;

11.6	We recommended and Management agreed that written justification be submitted by the following:
The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) for the payment of heavy equipment to RedCat International Limited, a foreign supplier, instead to Avantrac Heavy Machinery, Inc., the winning local bidder and on the absence of Warranty Security for the procurement of heavy equipment;
The Municipal Mayor on the absence of date of acceptance per Notice of Delivery and Acceptance for the heavy equipment;
The certifying officials on the varying delivery dates per Certificate of Acceptance, Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment and NDAs;
The officials concerned on the non-imposition of liquidated damages on the delayed delivery of heavy equipment.

12.6	We recommended and Management agreed:
To submit a written explanation pertaining to the non-utilization of the unexpended amount of funds received from LBP and DBP;
That the MSWDO and MDDRMO immediately identify the affected families of Typhoon Odette who were not yet given any financial assistance by the LGU or are in most need of any financial assistance and immediately facilitate the distribution of financial assistance to these families.
